paint.shared.io

Class ExperimentInfoTableIO

  • java.lang.Object
    • paint.shared.io.BaseTableIO
      • paint.shared.io.ExperimentInfoTableIO

  • public class ExperimentInfoTableIO
extends BaseTableIO
    Provides table input/output utilities for ExperimentInfo records (per-recording metadata).

    This class enforces a fixed schema defined by EXPERIMENT_INFO_COLS and EXPERIMENT_INFO_TYPES. It supports:

    • Creating an empty table with the correct schema via emptyTable().
    • Converting between lists of ExperimentInfo objects and a Table via toTable(java.util.List) and toEntities(tech.tablesaw.api.Table).
    • Reading CSV files into validated tables via readCsv(java.nio.file.Path).
    • Appending rows from one table to another with type-safe coercion via appendInPlace(tech.tablesaw.api.Table, tech.tablesaw.api.Table).

    Validation ensures that column order, names, and types match the expected schema, while allowing some flexibility (e.g. INTEGER -> DOUBLE upcasts).

      • emptyTable

        public tech.tablesaw.api.Table emptyTable()
        Creates an empty Table with the Experiment Info schema.

        The table has all expected columns defined by EXPERIMENT_INFO_COLS and EXPERIMENT_INFO_TYPES, but contains zero rows.

        Returns:
        a new empty Table ready to receive rows with the Experiment Info schema

      • toTable

        public tech.tablesaw.api.Table toTable(List<ExperimentInfo> infos)
        Converts a list of ExperimentInfo objects into a Table with a fixed schema.

        Each ExperimentInfo is mapped to a single row in the table with the following columns:

        • Recording Name (String)
        • Condition Number (int)
        • Replicate Number (int)
        • Probe Name (String)
        • Probe Type (String)
        • Cell Type (String)
        • Adjuvant (String)
        • Concentration (double)
        • Process Flag (boolean)
        • Threshold (double)

        The schema is enforced by starting from an emptyTable() with all expected columns pre-defined.

        Parameters:
        infos - the list of ExperimentInfo objects to convert
        Returns:
        a Table containing one row per experiment

      • toEntities

        public List<ExperimentInfo> toEntities(tech.tablesaw.api.Table table)
        Converts a Table into a list of ExperimentInfo objects.

        The table is expected to have already been validated against the experiment schema. Each row is mapped to a new ExperimentInfo instance, with values extracted from the following columns:

        • Recording Name → ExperimentInfo.setRecordingName(String)
        • Condition Number → ExperimentInfo.setConditionNumber(int)
        • Replicate Number → ExperimentInfo.setReplicateNumber(int)
        • Probe Name → ExperimentInfo.setProbeName(String)
        • Probe Type → ExperimentInfo.setProbeType(String)
        • Cell Type → ExperimentInfo.setCellType(String)
        • Adjuvant → ExperimentInfo.setAdjuvant(String)
        • Concentration → ExperimentInfo.setConcentration(double)
        • Process Flag → ExperimentInfo.setProcessFlag(boolean)
        • Threshold → ExperimentInfo.setThreshold(double)
        Parameters:
        table - the validated table to convert
        Returns:
        a list of ExperimentInfo objects populated from the table rows

      • readCsv

        public tech.tablesaw.api.Table readCsv(Path csvPath)
                                throws IOException
        Reads a CSV file as a Table, enforcing the Experiment Info schema.

        The schema is defined by EXPERIMENT_INFO_COLS (column names) and EXPERIMENT_INFO_TYPES (column types). Header order and types are validated before returning the table.

        Parameters:
        csvPath - the path to the CSV file
        Returns:
        a Table containing the experiment info data
        Throws:
        IOException - if the file cannot be read or parsed

      • appendInPlace

        public void appendInPlace(tech.tablesaw.api.Table target,
                          tech.tablesaw.api.Table source)
        Appends all rows from a source Table into a target Table, enforcing the Experiment Info schema.

        Behavior:

        • Rows are appended one by one to the target.
        • Columns are matched against EXPERIMENT_INFO_COLS with types from EXPERIMENT_INFO_TYPES.
        • If the source table is missing a column, that column is skipped.
        • Missing cell values in the source remain missing in the destination.
        • INTEGER -> DOUBLE upcasts are allowed when the schema expects a double.
        • Other type mismatches throw an IllegalArgumentException.
        Overrides:
        appendInPlace in class BaseTableIO
        Parameters:
        target - the destination table to which rows will be appended
        source - the source table providing rows and column values
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the source contains an unsupported column type
